Barclays, Rio, Ryanair, Shell: U.K., Irish Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S a r a h   H a l l s   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-09-02T06:50:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/barclays-rio-ryanair-shell-u-k-irish-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  Futures on the benchmark FTSE 100 Index retreated 1.1
percent to 5,335 at 7:49 a.m. in London. The FTSE 100 advanced
24.12 points, or 0.5 percent, to 5,418.65 yesterday. The FTSE
All-Share Index rose 0.4 percent to 2,812.61, while Ireland’s
ISEQ Index gained 1 percent to 2,602.01.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  : The U.K. bank and five other
companies were sued by the trustee liquidating the money
management firm of convicted Ponzi scheme mastermind  Bernard
Madoff , according to court records.  Separately, Barclays Capital hired Charlie Berman as head
of public sector for Europe, the  Middle East  and Africa. He sits
within the global finance unit. The shares jumped 5.6 percent to
180.35 pence.  BP Plc (BP/)   and  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA)  : The
oil companies began evacuating workers from platforms and rigs
in the Gulf of Mexico as a storm intensified in the largest U.S.
crude-producing region. BP fell 3.5 percent to 388.5 pence.
Shell rose 0.5 percent to 2,075 pence.  Rio Tinto Group (RIO LN): The world’s second-largest mining
company paid this year’s highest rent for a capesize vessel to
carry iron ore to China from Australia, potentially signaling an
end to slumping hire costs for dry-bulk ships. The shares
dropped 0.9 percent to 3,768.5 pence.  Ryanair Holdings Plc (RYA)  : Europe’s biggest discount
airline said it is surprised the U.K.’s Office of Fair Trading
is examining a failed merger offer between it and  Aer Lingus (AERL) 
Group Plc Ryanair gained 0.4 percent to 3.14 euros.
Aer Lingus rose 0.8 percent to 65 euro cents.  Tullow Oil Plc (TLW)  : Chinese oil explorer, Cnooc Ltd.
will make a takeover bid for the U.K.-based company, according
to a report in the Independent newspaper. The shares jumped 3.2
percent to 1,109 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
